NAME
    Dist::Zilla::Role::CheckPackageDeclared - Role to check if a package is
    provided by your distribution

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.001 of
    Dist::Zilla::Role::CheckPackageDeclared (from Perl distribution
    Dist-Zilla-Role-CheckPackageDeclared), released on 2018-06-26.

METHODS
  is_package_declared
    Usage: my $declared = $obj->is_package_declared($package) => bool

    Return true when $package is declared by one of the modules in the
    distribution. Module::Metadata is used to extract declared packages in a
    file.

